name: Rohu/seelavathi curry cut with head
description: Full body (Head, Tel, Belly and Shoulder) No Selection Issue.Rohu fish is a full fish weight around 1Kg. The item is dressed, cleaned and then cut into medium sizes after dresseing and cleaning 10% weight will be lose. It is rich in proteins and low in fat. It also contains plenty of minerals such as zinc, iron and calcium, and has an abundance of omega-3 fatty acids. Vitamins such as A and D are also present. It helps increase the absorption rate, boosts immunity and has anti-inflammatory properties. It also enhances the skin, nails and hair, regulates blood sugar and prevents cardiovascular disease. Rohu fish is a delicacy in the regions of Assam and Orissa. It is very popular in Bengali cuisine - served with mustard oil gravy. They otherwise can be served fried or grilled.

name: Rohu/seelavathi curry cut with head skinless
description:
The flesh of rohu is white, non-oily, tender, smooth in texture and mild with practically no “fishy” taste. Just about anyone should find it enjoyable.
Rohu is enriched with a handsome amount of protein and packed with Omega 3 fatty acids and vitamins A, B, and C.
